t be done when you continue to do mobs and epics that are trivial or that don't benefit the guild (whatever that means). They need to make the epic mobs harder and spawnable in easy in the non-planar zones plain and simple but VI feels it necessary to make a FICTIONAL game have a realistic edge by showing you can't get what you want unless you wait long enough (in otherwords pay them enought money per month) or stay up an insane amount of hours to get an ultra-rare mob to spawn just to find out he dropped his common drop or was ks'ed.<br>
<br>
Got a tad off topic but my basic thoughts are eliminate the need to go to planes for epic pieces. Make planes essentially for gear like HoT or Kael. It's so sad I have pretty much decided what I will be doing is parking one of my characters I play a lot up in hate and leaving his ass up there until I get the staff.<br>
<br>
What I find is funny is if the other epics were that comparable to the mage epic there is NO WAY the Everquest community would allow VI to bend them over like this.<br>
<br>
If anything make the Magi more common, been to hate and checked on mobs in hate enough to know he should have been on.<br>
<br>
Last thought: With a proposed idea of a 2nd epic coming out with the release of PoP, how do you feel about your guildies getting their 2nd part of their epic before you even have your FIRST.<br>
